{"title":"Esker Cycles 2024 Lorax Titanium Drop Bar MTB","link":"https://theradavist.com/esker-cycles-lorax-titanium/","date":1716907543000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1542\" height=\"1028\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/EskerLorax_Titanium.jpg?fit=1200,1028&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/EskerLorax_Titanium.jpg?w=1542&amp;quality=75 1542w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/EskerLorax_Titanium.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/EskerLorax_Titanium.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/EskerLorax_Titanium.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><em>Esker Cycles’ Lorax is back and better than ever. The <a href=\"https://eskercycles.com/pages/lorax-ti\" target=\"_blank\">2024 Esker Cycles Lorax Titanium</a> is a boost drop bar MTB, with touring accouterments, and a 120 mm suspension corrected fork, designed for long-distance touring and adventure riding. Let’s take a closer look…</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1983\" height=\"1322\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/EskerLoraxTi_Frameset.jpg?fit=1200,1322&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/EskerLoraxTi_Frameset.jpg?w=1983&amp;quality=75 1983w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/EskerLoraxTi_Frameset.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/EskerLoraxTi_Frameset.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/EskerLoraxTi_Frameset.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<h3>Esker Cycles Lorax Ti Chassis Quick Hits</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>29″ wheels for 2.2-2.6″ tires</li>\n<li>Boost-Spacing</li>\n<li>Drop bar Mountain Touring Bike – Made for 495 mm length rigid forks, and can accommodate up to 120 mm suspension fork</li>\n<li>3/2.5 Seamless Butted Titanium Frame – custom-shaped and butted titanium for the best in ride quality and durability</li>\n<li>Portage Dropout – for flexibility to many different uses. Lorax includes Fixed position UDH dropouts with Flat Mount brake</li>\n<li>Lotsa mounts – Top Tube Bag, two sets of 3-pack mounts, and full Rack and Fender mounting points mean you can carry just about anything</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/EskerLoraxTi_Details.jpeg?fit=1200,1365&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/EskerLoraxTi_Details.jpeg?w=2048&amp;quality=75 2048w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/EskerLoraxTi_Details.jpeg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/EskerLoraxTi_Details.jpeg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/EskerLoraxTi_Details.jpeg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/EskerLoraxTi_Details.jpeg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>This go-anywhere dropbar mountain bike can take you from your town trails to the Tour Divide and everywhere in between. The Lorax is equipped with everything you would expect from an Esker: External cable routing, a threaded bottom bracket, and 44mm head tube. The Lorax also has 22 attachment points for all of your adventure accessories. This also includes top tube, rack, and fender mounts built into the frame.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1983\" height=\"1322\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/Lorax_Geometry_2.jpg?fit=1200,1322&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/Lorax_Geometry_2.jpg?w=1983&amp;quality=75 1983w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/Lorax_Geometry_2.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/Lorax_Geometry_2.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/Lorax_Geometry_2.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2766\" height=\"1844\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/Lorax_Geometry.jpg?fit=1200,1844&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/Lorax_Geometry.jpg?w=2766&amp;quality=75 2766w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/Lorax_Geometry.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/Lorax_Geometry.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/Lorax_Geometry.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/Lorax_Geometry.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/Lorax_Geometry.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<h3>Lorax Ti Geometry</h3>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2048\" height=\"2048\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/EskerLorax_Details.jpeg?fit=1200,2048&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/EskerLorax_Details.jpeg?w=2048&amp;quality=75 2048w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/EskerLorax_Details.jpeg?resize=1200,1200&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/EskerLorax_Details.jpeg?resize=2000,2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/EskerLorax_Details.jpeg?resize=150,150&amp;quality=75 150w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/EskerLorax_Details.jpeg?resize=768,768&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/EskerLorax_Details.jpeg?resize=1536,1536&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /> <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2048\" height=\"2048\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/EskerLorax_Details2.jpeg?fit=1200,2048&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/EskerLorax_Details2.jpeg?w=2048&amp;quality=75 2048w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/EskerLorax_Details2.jpeg?resize=1200,1200&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/EskerLorax_Details2.jpeg?resize=2000,2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/EskerLorax_Details2.jpeg?resize=150,150&amp;quality=75 150w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/EskerLorax_Details2.jpeg?resize=768,768&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/EskerLorax_Details2.jpeg?resize=1536,1536&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /> <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2048\" height=\"2048\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/image-2.jpg?fit=1200,2048&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/image-2.jpg?w=2048&amp;quality=75 2048w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/image-2.jpg?resize=1200,1200&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/image-2.jpg?resize=2000,2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/image-2.jpg?resize=150,150&amp;quality=75 150w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/image-2.jpg?resize=768,768&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/05/image-2.jpg?resize=1536,1536&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<h3>Esker Cycles Lorax Ti Specs:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Frame Material: Seamless, double-butted 3/2.5 Titanium</li>\n<li>Weight: 2,855 grams for Medium, or 6.29lbs – Weight includes dropouts, axle, seat collar, and cable guides</li>\n<li>Frame Includes: Wolf Tooth seatpost collar, rear axle, Adjustable UDH Portage Dropout, cable guides and bolts</li>\n<li>Headtube Diameter: 44mm ID, 50mm OD</li>\n<li>Rear Dropout Spacing: 148mm</li>\n<li>BB Type: Threaded 73mm English</li>\n<li>Headset Lower Stack Height: 13mm</li>\n<li>Tire Size: Designed around 29×2.2″ Accomodates up to 29×2.6″ depending on tire and rim choice.</li>\n<li>Seatpost: 34.9 clamp, 31.6 post, internally routed</li>\n<li>Thru Axle: Boost 148 / 180mm / M12x1.0</li>\n<li>Max Chainring: 40t round / 38t oval / Boost Chainline</li>\n<li>Brake Mount: Flat Mount, 160mm rotor native OR Post Mount, 180mm rotor native</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p><em>Check out more at <a href=\"https://eskercycles.com/pages/lorax-ti\" target=\"_blank\">Esker Cycles</a>.</em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/esker-cycles-lorax-titanium/\">Esker Cycles 2024 Lorax Titanium Drop Bar MTB</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"4e7216846edc93538063ffbe98ada2e15762b11899861ce34b485e0c84a127e8","category":"Cycling"}